Description: Make "set" method of class "Filter" public.
 Some packages (for example unity-scope-home) fail to compile due to missing
 unavailable setter for class "Filter".

 This patch makes setter of "Filter" class public so that other packages can
 use it.
Author: Tomasz Jeruzalski <tomekdev17@gmail.com>
Bug: https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/libunity/+bug/2141346
Last-Update: 2026-02-16
---
--- a/src/unity-filters.vala
+++ b/src/unity-filters.vala
@@ -76,7 +76,7 @@
   public FilterRenderer renderer { get; construct; }
   public bool visible { get; construct set; }
   public bool collapsed { get; internal construct set; }
-  public bool filtering { get; internal construct set; }
+  public bool filtering { get; construct set; }
 
   public signal void changed ();
   
